Face-to-face communication is considered the richest form of information because it includes **nonverbal cues, tone, and immediate feedback**, making it the most nuanced and effective for complex interactions. While video conferences (D) come close, they lack the full physical presence and spontaneity of in-person communication. Telephone (A) and email (C) are far less rich due to their limited sensory input.
